spe.ch.single.coph <- cophenetic(spe.ch.single) #  - Single linkage clustering

## [1] 0.599193

## [1] 0.7655628

cor(spe.ch, spe.ch.UPGMA.coph) #  - 'pearson'
## [1] 0.8608326
spe.ch.ward.coph <- cophenetic(spe.ch.ward) # Ward
cor(spe.ch, spe.ch.ward.coph) #  - 'pearson'
## [1] 0.7998516

# --- 2 ---
# Adjacency matrix from the "a" distance matrix
#     -- test.a.R test.R()
adjm2 <- 1 - as.matrix(res$p.a.dist) # 
adjm2[adjm2 < 0.5] <- 0
diag(adjm2) <- 0 # 

# --- 3 ---
# Adjacency matrix from the Spearman rank correlation matrix
#  Spearman   
adjm3 <- cor(spe, # 
             method = "spearman")
#  rho > 0.2
adjm2[adjm3 < 0.25] <- 0
adjm2[adjm3 >= 0.25] <- 1  # binary co-occurrences | /
diag(adjm3) <- 0 #

iv <- iva$indcls[pval.adj <= 0.05]
pv <- iva$pval[pval.adj <= 0.05]
fr <- apply(spe > 0, 2, sum)[pval.adj <= 0.05] # apply  
fidg <- data.frame(
  group = gr,
  indval = iv,
  pvalue = pv,
  freq = fr
